
/*
STEPS TO GET THE GOOGLE-SERVICES.JSON FILE FROM FIREBASE:

1. Go to the Firebase Console (https://console.firebase.google.com/).
2. Select your project. If you haven't created one, click "Add project" and follow the setup.
3. Click the "Settings" gear icon in the left sidebar and select "Project settings".
4. Scroll down to the "Your apps" section.
5. If you haven't added an Android app yet:
   - Click the Android icon (or "Add app").
   - Enter your Android package name (found in your app's build.gradle).
   - Click "Register app".
6. Once the app is registered, you will see a button labeled "Download google-services.json".
7. Click the button to download the file.
8. Move the downloaded file into your project's 'app' directory (or the path specified in your local environment).
*/
